abstract: >-
  Policy Prism is an open-source research platform for critical analysis
  of AI governance policy. It operationalises Actor-Network Theory and
  Assemblage Theory through a coordinated LLM ensemble and an eight-layer
  analytical framework, enabling multi-lens analysis, ghost node detection
  (GNDP v1.0), ecosystem mapping, translational stratification theory,
  and comparative synthesis across jurisdictions.
